/apr/14/russia-porn-ban-tatarstan|title=Century-old law cited in request to ban 136 porn sites from Republic of Tatarstan|date=14 April 2014|publisher=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://izvestia.ru/news/585309|date=13 April 2015|publisher=[[Izvestia]]|script-title=ru:\u0420\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0430\u0434\u0437\u043e\u0440 \u0432\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0443 136 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0432 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a|trans-title=Roskomnadzor will add 136 pornographic sites to the blacklist|last=Zykov|first=Vladimir|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nLegislation to restrict pornographic sites include efforts targeted at reducing [[human trafficking]] which may mandate electronic manufactures to install content filters to restrict \"obscene\" material. Nevertheless, organizations in support of free speech have been speaking out against the efforts to include porn sites such as xHamster which noted 125 million clicks from Thailand and 95 million clicks from users in Turkey in which the site is banned.<ref>{{cite web|title=Porn Ban: Free Speech Groups, Porn Sites Oppose Legislation To Block 'Obscene' Content|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/porn-ban-free-speech-groups-porn-sites-oppose-legislation-block-obscene-content-2524767|publisher=International Business Times|accessdate=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nOther attempts at censoring has its basis in violating [[net neutrality]], whereby governments may restrict bandwidth to various Internet categories. xHamster's Alex Hawkins stated, \"As an international company, we see every day how restrictive governments use regulatory tools, like traffic throttling, to limit access to not only porn but political speech.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Porn Companies Tell Us Why the End of Net Neutrality Will Make Porn Boring|url=https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/mbjyx4/porn-companies-tell-us-why-the-end-of-net-neutrality-will-make-porn-boring|publisher=Motherboard|accessdate=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIndia blocked xHamster again in late 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenextweb.com/syndication/2019/01/26/indias-porn-crackdown-isnt-working-but-chinas-is/|title=India\u2019s porn crackdown isn\u2019t working \u2014 but China\u2019s is|last=SEXTECHGUIDE|date=2019-01-26|website=The Next Web|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n===Copyright infringement===\nIn 2011, xHamster was sued by Fraserside Holdings, Ltd., a producer of adult films and a subsidiary of [[Private Media Group, Inc.|Private Media Group Inc.]]<ref>{{cite web |title=COMPLAINT and Jury Demand|url=https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/Iowa_Northern_District_Court/3--11-cv-03025/Fraserside_IP_LLC_v._Hammy_Media_Ltd_et_al/2/ |publisher=Docket Alarm|accessdate=2 January 2017}}</ref> Fraserside and Private alleged that xHamster had infringed their copyrights by streaming copies of their adult media over the Internet. Fraserside brought the case in Iowa, and in 2012 Judge Mark Bennett found that U.S. courts lacked jurisdiction over xHamster because it is a Cyprus-based company with \"no offices in Iowa, no employees in Iowa, no telephone number in Iowa[;] ... xHamster does not advertise in Iowa[;] No xHamster officer or director has ever visited Iowa[; and] ... All of xHamster's servers are located outside of the United States.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Memorandum re Defendant's Motion to Dismiss|url=https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/Iowa_Northern_District_Court/3--11-cv-03025/Fraserside_IP_LLC_v._Hammy_Media_Ltd_et_al/50/|website=Docket Alarm|accessdate=2 January 2017}}</ref> The copyright infringement case was dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fraserside IP LLC v. Hammy Media Ltd et al|url=https://www.docketalarm.com/cases/Iowa_Northern_District_Court/3--11-cv-03025/Fraserside_IP_LLC_v._Hammy_Media_Ltd_et_al/|accessdate=2 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Pornographic video digital distribution platforms}}\n\n[[Category:Cypriot erotica and pornography websites]]\n[[Category:Gratis pornography]]\n[[Category:Video hosting]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2007]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in Cyprus]]\n", "text_old": "{{press release|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|pornographic video sharing website}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = xHamster\n| logo             = XHamster logo.svg\n| screenshot       = \n| caption          = \n| url              = {{URL|https://xhamster.com}}\n| type             = Pornographic [[video sharing]]\n| registration     = Optional\n| language         = English, German, French, Spanish, Italian, Portuguese, Polish, Russian, Japanese, Dutch, Afrikaans\n| content_license  = Free pornography\n| owner            = Hammy Media Ltd<ref name=\"TNW-BW\"/>\n| location_city    = [[Limassol]]\n| location_country = Cyprus\n| author           = \n| revenue          = \n| alexa            = {{decrease}} 107<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/xhamster.com|title=XHamster Traffic, Demographics and Competitors|work=[[Alexa Internet]]|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> {{small|(March 2020)}}\n| launch_date      = {{start date and age|df=yes|2007|4|2}}\n| current_status   = Online\n}}\n'''xHamster''' is a [[Pornography|pornographic]] media and [[social networking]] site headquartered in the Cypriot city of [[Limassol]],<ref name=\"TNW-BW\"/> with offices in [[Houston]], [[Kyoto]], and [[London]]. xHamster serves user-submitted pornographic videos, [[webcam model]]s, pornographic photographs, and [[erotic literature]], and incorporates social networking features. xHamster was founded in 2007. With more than 10 million members, it is the third most popular pornography website on the Internet after [[XVideos]] and [[Pornhub]]. As of March 2020, xHamster was the 22nd most trafficked website in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.similarweb.com/website/xhamster.com|title=https://www.similarweb.com/website/xhamster.com|website=www.similarweb.com|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> \n\nThe site produces ''[[The Sex Factor]]'', a [[reality TV]] series in which men and women compete to become [[porn stars]]. The site has been targeted as part of [[malvertising]] campaigns, and some governments have blocked xHamster as part of larger initiatives against [[Internet pornography]].\n\n==History==\nIn early 2007, a group of anonymous individuals decided to create a new adult video service,<ref name=TNW-BW/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://xhamster.com/about.php|title=About Us|website=xHamster|accessdate=4 July 2016}}</ref> and xHamster was launched on 2 April 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://whois.domaintools.com/xhamster.com|title=XHamster.com WHOIS, DNS, & Domain Info - DomainTools|work=[[WHOIS]]|date=2016|accessdate=21 February 2016}}</ref> xHamster was envisioned as a [[social network]]; a spokesperson said the site's content organization scheme was intended to allow \"people who wanted to chat, exchange erotic pics and share amateur videos ... to find mutual friends online and maybe discover partners interested in intimate relationships.\"<ref name=TNW-BW>{{cite web|url=https://thenextweb.com/insider/2016/03/03/the-almost-invisible-men-and-women-behind-the-worlds-largest-porn-sites/|title=The (almost) invisible men and women behind the world\u2019s largest porn sites|website=The Next Web|date=3 March 2016|author=Ben Woods}}</ref> Surpassing 10 million members in 2015, xHamster became the third most popular pornography Internet website, after [[XVideos]] and [[Pornhub]].<ref name=\"TNW-BW\"/> In May 2016, xHamster launched ''[[The Sex Factor]]'', a reality series competition where contestants compete to become a [[porn star]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/belle-knox-host-x-rated-reality-show-sex-factor-article-1.1808954|title=Belle Knox to host X-rated reality show, \u2018The Sex Factor\u2019|publisher=|accessdate=30 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2014/05/30/porn-star-belle-knox-to-host-racy-reality-show/ |title=Porn star Belle Knox to host racy reality show|publisher=Fox News|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/53171/duke-porn-star-sex-factor-porn-reality-tv/|title=Belle Knox: Duke Porn Star Lands Hosting Gig on Porn Reality Show|author=Michelle Arrouas|work=TIME.com|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nxHamster has restricted access to its site and removed content in response to political issues concerning the [[LGBT community]] and [[rape culture]]. The site blocked users with IP addresses based in [[North Carolina]] during April 2016, after the state enacted a law that stopped its counties and cities from passing laws to protect [[LGBT]] people.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bruce Springsteen or porn site, who will get North Carolina to change its anti-LGBT laws? |url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/world/2016/04/12/Bruce-Springsteen-or-porn-site-who-will-get-North-Carolina-to-change-its-anti-LGBT-laws |accessdate=12 April 2016 |work=Times Live|date=12 April 2016}}</ref> In response to the verdict of the ''[[People v. Turner]]'' sexual assault case, xHamster instituted a \"Brock Turner rule\", which banned videos involving [[rape]], including those involving sex with an unconscious partner or hypnosis.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/xhamster-crack-down-rape-porn-adopts-brock-turner-rule-1565438|title=xHamster to crack down on rape porn, adopts 'Brock Turner Rule'|last=Russon|first=Mary-Ann|date=14 June 2016|publisher=[[International Business Times]]}}</ref> In the aftermath of the [[2016 Democratic National Committee email leak]], xHamster offered [[Debbie Wasserman Schultz]] a US$50,000 role in a pornographic film with a [[Bernie Sanders]] lookalike.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailydot.com/irl/debbie-wasserman-schultz-porn/|title=Debbie Wasserman Schultz has a new job offer: $50,000 to do porn|publisher=[[The Daily Dot]]|date=26 July 2016|first=Lyz|last=Lenz}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, Alex Hawkins stated that xHamster would be sponsoring a trip for [[Brendan Dassey]] to [[Wrestlemania]]. He stated \"We are pleased that we can make this young man's dream of going to Wrestlemania come true... We have been in talks with the family and they are more than thrilled that Brendan will get this opportunity after so many years of heartache and injustice.\" The idea was started by a change.org petition.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Salo |first1=Jackie |title=Porn site wants to send Brendan Dassey to Wrestlemania |url=https://nypost.com/2016/08/23/porn-site-wants-to-send-brendan-dassey-to-wrestlemania/ |publisher=NY Post}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2016, Alex Hawkins speaking for xHamster confirmed that they had purchased a sex tape alleged to portray American actress [[Alexis Arquette]], which was put up for sale by an ex-lover shortly after her death. xHamster destroyed all copies of it, announcing that \"Ms. Arquette was an icon and activist in the [[transgender|trans]] community and we could not see someone smear her memory the way the selling party was trying to do.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com.au/entry/alexis-arquette-sex-tape-report_us_57dabeede4b08cb14094251c?section=us_queer-voices|title = Porn Site Buys Alexis Arquette Sex Tape But Not For The Reason You'd Think|date = 17 September 2016|accessdate = 18 September 2016|newspaper = [[Huffington Post]]|last = Wong|first = Curtis.}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, xHamster held auditions for U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], Trump's family members, and Trump cabinet member lookalikes. The winners will be cast in porn parodies. Alex Hawkins said, \"there is nothing more that the American public needs than quality adult content parodies to help them understand the ever shifting landscape of their Executive Branch of government.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gardner|first1=Lucy|title=Porn site holds Donald Trump lookalike auditions to hire X-rated actor for series of presidential parodies|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/weird-news/porn-site-holds-donald-trump-9766866|publisher=Mirror.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rense|first1=Sarah|title=Do You Have What It Takes to Be a Donald Trump Porn Impersonator?|url=http://www.esquire.com/lifestyle/sex/news/a50967/donald-trump-porn/|publisher=Esquire|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Micklethwaite|first1=Jamie |title=Porn site wants Donald Trump lookalike 'with small hands' to star in X-rated series|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/586657/Donald-Trump-Ivanka-Trump-Melania-Trump-porn-hardcore-Xhamster |publisher=Daily Star}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=KHAL|title=A Porn Site Wants a Trump Look-Alike With Small Hands for New Movie|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2017/02/donald-trump-adult-film-site-look-alike-new-movie|publisher=Complex|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref> In March 2017 John Brutal, a dialysis worker in Minnesota, was selected as the winning contestant to perform the part.<ref>{{cite web|title=This 27-Year-Old Just Won A Contest To Play Trump|url=http://www.vocativ.com/412514/new-porn-donald-trump-john-brutal/|publisher=Vocativ|accessdate=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nDuring the total [[solar eclipse of 21 August 2017]] xHamster reported significant decrease in site usage across the United States: cities in range of totality such as Nashville, Tennessee, had a viewership drop 43%. Charleston, South Carolina, and Portland, Oregon, saw drops of 36% and 35% respectively, jumping back up to 85% increase in Charleston and 63% in Portland after the eclipse. Cities outside the path of totality experienced a less drastic change, with cities such as New York and Los Angeles, which experiencing 15% less viewership.<ref>{{cite web|title=The eclipse actually got people to stop watching